        "timestamp": "2022-09-30 15:43:35.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-2\n\n(8 comments)\n\nI've found some problems:\n- The TOSCA function is not being reloaded. Along with that, if I save again the input information is lost when it is a TOSCA function.\n- When it is reloaded in the screen, it does not show the value as a TOSCA function.\n- When I set a TOSCA function value to an input property, it saves the value of it as a TOSCA function object. I believe a more complex handling is needed to store and retrieve input properties values as TOSCA function.\n- When the TOSCA is exported, it comes with the TOSCA function object information instead the correct TOSCA function syntax.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
